    {
      "id": "twilite-edge-template-set-proposal-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": -160
      },
      "width": 640,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Proposal Shape\n\nClass-based edges are now part of the system substrate.\n\nThe template library should guarantee that:\n- edge classes can be defined and exposed consistently\n- edge classes show up in the legend with a real preview (SVG stroke data)\n- assigning an edge class from edge properties is stable and reversible\n- plain edges remain valid and require no class\n\n## Canonical Templates Needed Now\n\n- **plain edge baseline**: the default edge without a class\n- **edge class artifact template**: a TTV-shaped edge-class graph (like `task.depends-on`) with render defaults and legend preview data\n- **edge class bridge + smoke template**: a minimal graph that consumes edge classes via bridge and proves legend + authoring flow\n\n## Structural Consequence\n\nThe node template set should now treat this edge template set as a prerequisite. We should update node templates only after these edge paths are embodied in reusable template structure.\n\n## Consequence\n\nThis work should land before broader UI refactors and before broader node-template cleanup, because edge properties, legend rendering, and template structure all depend on it.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "twilite-edge-template-set-proposal-plain",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Plain Edge",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 340,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Plain Edge Baseline\n\nPlain edges must remain valid.\n\nTemplate requirement:\n- define the default edge semantics and minimum render surface\n- ensure the legend preview for an unclassified edge is still readable\n- serve as the default relationship pattern inside node templates unless a class-backed edge is explicitly needed\n\nThis is a template because it becomes the fallback behavior everywhere else.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "twilite-edge-template-set-proposal-edge-class",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Edge Class Template",
      "position": {
        "x": 1120,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Edge Class Artifact Template\n\nWe have working edge-class artifacts already (for example `task.depends-on`).\n\nTemplate requirement:\n- standardize the required nodes/fields for edge class identity\n- require `renderDefaults` and legend preview data to be authored as SVG (not inferred)\n- ensure the edge class exposes port/node/icon surfaces consistently\n- provide the canonical artifact shape that node templates will consume through bridge structure\n\nThis should become the canonical scaffolding for new edge classes.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "twilite-edge-template-set-proposal-smoke",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Smoke Template",
      "position": {
        "x": 1520,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 340,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Edge Class Smoke Template\n\nTemplate requirement:\n- a minimal graph that bridges in edge classes\n- verifies edge class shows in the legend\n- verifies legend preview matches the actual rendered edge\n- provides a stable place to test class assignment and view switching in edge properties\n- doubles as the reference pattern that updated node templates should imitate when they include class-backed edges\n\nThis is the guardrail against regressions.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
